The paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves optimization and automated mechanism design, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The concept of budget balance is often studied in the context of economics and market design, which falls under the category of algorithmic game theory (cs.EC). The paper also uses mathematical tools such as optimization and probability theory, which are relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
